Ad Text:
Why work for Neumann Steel?
You would be working for one of the most reputable family owned and operated companies first established on the Gold Coast over 50 years ago. We specialise in steel reinforcing and plastic accessory products in the QLD and NSW markets. Our highly integrated supply chain is supported by our experienced staff and a wealth of industry knowledge.
  
With a people-first mindset, Neumann Steel is dedicated to supporting the local community and fostering long-lasting relationships while delivering quality commercial and residential projects in the spirit of openness and honesty. We strive to build a rewarding, inclusive, and inspiring culture, with innovation at the forefront of mind.




Quick overview of the role 
We are currently seeking an experienced Data Analyst to join our ICT team in a full-time capacity.  This role is responsible for the architect and implementation of a scalable data warehouse, consolidating data from multiple sources. This position is based at our Currumbin Head Office on the Gold Coast.

What will you be doing?

Develop and maintain PowerBI reports that provide clear, actionable insights for each business unit.
Collaborate with stakeholders to define reporting requirements and ensure alignment with business objectives.
Automate data refresh processes and optimise performance for real-time analytics
Design and implement automated workflows using Power Automate to streamline data processes and reporting.
Integrate Power Platform solutions with other Microsoft and third-party systems (e.g. SharePoint, Dynamics 365, Teams)
Provide ongoing support, training and documentation for end-users and team members.
Maintain up-to-date knowledge of Power platforms features, updates and bet practices.
Collaborate with Data Partners, Product Champions and project teams to promote adoption of data standards.
Document data models, ETL processes and reporting standards.
Analyse business/system processes using various methods such as gap analysis or PDCA to find opportunities for improvement, via reporting dashboards and automation.



What are we looking for in the successful candidate?

Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, IT, Engineering, Business Analytics, or related field (or equivalent experience).
Strong experience in data engineering, data analysis, and analytics projects, including Microsoft Fabric, SQL Server, ETL tools, DAX, T-SQL, and performance optimisation.
Advanced SQL skills and solid understanding of data architecture, data warehousing, and Azure cloud technologies.
Proven ability to analyse complex business processes, identify inefficiencies, and translate requirements into technical solutions (automation, reporting, dashboards).
Skilled in Power BI, Power Automate, Power Apps, and workflow automation; MS Power BI and Power Automate certifications preferred.
Experience collaborating with both business and technical teams, with strong communication, stakeholder management, and documentation skills.
Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines, DevOps, Microsoft 365 (SharePoint, Teams, Outlook), scripting languages (PowerShell, JavaScript), and agile methodologies.

What’s in it for you

Free parking onsite
Free lunch on Friday’s!
Mental health and wellbeing support, wellness discounts for mind, body, work, and life, including an Employee Assistance Program

Our culture is driven by our values. We value high performance, collaboration, innovation, integrity and respect. Working for us means being part of a great team of people and we believe our people are our biggest asset. If you think you would be able to complement our awesome team, then we’d like to hear from you.

Ad Text:
The role: 

Two Principal Business Analyst positions available:

1 x 23/08/2026

1 x 23/02/2027

Reporting to the Project Director, you will be responsible to lead business analysis activities for one or more cyber initiatives, delivering high-quality requirements and process designs for large-scale ICT Cyber Security projects. You will be responsible for the end-to-end analysis lifecycle—including Business case development, requirements elicitation and validation, gap analysis, and future-state modelling—with a focus on key cyber security technologies like Multi-Factor Authentication, Data Loss Prevention, Network Security and Entra ID. You are expected to ensure the delivery of valued, integrated and effective business solution to the program/project(s).

Is this opportunity for you?

To be a successful candidate for this role, you will have proven experience in the end-to-end business analysis artifacts lifecycle management, preferably across cyber security projects and/or within the Healthcare industry.

The ideal candidate will have demonstrated skills and experience across the following:

Demonstrate experience leading and managing business analysis activities within IM/ICT projects preferably in the Cyber Security domain.
Expertise in navigating high-complexity organizational structures to lead requirements discovery and process optimization. You are adept at facilitating executive-level workshops to reconcile competing stakeholder priorities, translating ambiguous business needs into rigorous, validated functional and technical specifications for enterprise-grade Cyber Security deployments.
Demonstrate high level knowledge and application of appropriate business analysis frameworks, and an ability to promote and provide advice on the use of appropriate techniques, methodologies, and tools, preferably aligned with Business Analysis Body of Knowledge Version 3.0 (BABOK).
Proven expertise in leading business process modelling and requirements definition within large, complex environment.
Proven ability to lead, manage and mentor a multi-disciplinary team, developing effective working relationships with team members and stakeholders including mentoring other business analysts within the organisation.

The following experience will be highly regarded:

Demonstrated experience in developing and delivering robust, complex business cases for large scale, enterprise-wide technology or security transformation initiatives.
Demonstrated domain knowledge across strategic cyber security planning, including risk management frameworks, financial justification of security controls and modern security architecture concepts.
Prior experience and knowledge in the cyber security technologies, specifically across RSA SecureID, Data Loss Prevention, MFA or Microsoft EntraID.

Key Responsibilities:

Fulfil the responsibilities of this role in accordance with QPS values as outlined above.
Provide high level expertise, analysis, coordination, and support for the timely delivery of project artifacts within business analysis remit.
Lead the analysis of business requirements and system specifications and provide expertise to ensure specifications are aligned to business requirements.
Elicit and document functional and non-functional requirements, configuration and integration specifications and traceability matrix.
Establish and maintain productive professional networks across eHealth, Hospital and Health Services, the Department of Health and other key stakeholders to foster ongoing collaboration and enhance organisational maturity.
Review key artifacts produced by external vendors to identify gaps and improve document quality.

While experience in health care is not a mandatory requirement, we highly value candidates who have demonstrated relevant experience in clinical systems, health IT, or digital health. If your experience is in other sectors, please make sure to outline how your knowledge can transfer to the healthcare context.

Benefits of working with eHealth Queensland:

By joining eHealth Queensland, you will work within a fast-paced, challenging and supportive environment where every employee plays a critical role in our ongoing success.

You will enjoy a variety of benefits, including:

Competitive salary + generous superannuation and leave loading
Flexible working arrangements
Diverse work culture
Career training and development

Senior Change Analyst - current NV1 clearance preferred


Job Title: Change Manager
Location: Sydney (3 days per week onsite)
Contract Length: 12 months (with extensions until 2029)
Day Rate: $700 per day inc super



About

This role supports a large-scale Governance, Risk and Compliance (GRC) transformation program introducing a new service model, changes to roles and responsibilities, and the replacement of core systems used to manage risks, controls, obligations, incidents, and audits.

The change will impact staff across both corporate functions and operational business groups. The program is technology-enabled, data-driven, and focused on embedding new ways of working alongside the rollout of an integrated risk and compliance platform.

The Senior Change Analyst will sit within an IT and Digital portfolio, reporting into a Change Manager and working closely with a large, multidisciplinary delivery team and an extensive SME network. This is a 12-month engagement within a long-term transformation roadmap.

Responsibilities

Establish and maintain stakeholder communication and engagement plans for organisation-wide change
Support change stream planning and coordination using tools such as Excel and MS Planner, including sprint and delivery boards
Develop and deliver change communications including presentations, emails, intranet content, and supporting materials (video development skills highly regarded)
Contribute to change impact assessments across corporate and operational business groups, including changes to service models, roles, and responsibilities
Support and help facilitate change workshops, engagement sessions, and stakeholder forums
Work closely with Change Managers, Project Managers, Business Analysts, and Technical Specialists to align change activity with delivery milestones
Analyse and manage people and adoption-related data to inform change planning, readiness, and reporting
Use Excel, Power BI, and PowerApps to slice, analyse, and present data to support decision-making
Coordinate laterally across large delivery teams and SME groups to ensure consistency of messaging and approach
Support change governance, reporting, and risk management activities

Experience

Around 5+ years total experience, with exposure to change, IT delivery, communications, project coordination, or similar environments
Experience supporting technology-enabled change within complex organisations
Solid core change capability, including exposure to impact assessment, stakeholder engagement, and adoption planning
Strong analytical skills, with confidence working hands-on with data and reporting
Advanced Excel capability; experience with Power BI, PowerApps, or similar tools is highly regarded
Strong written communication skills, with the ability to produce clear and engaging content for business audiences
Experience in governance, risk, compliance, or regulated environments is desirable but not essential
Experience operating within large corporate or enterprise environments

Why apply

Work on a meaningful, organisation-wide transformation
Exposure to both operating model change and system replacement
Collaborate with experienced change and delivery professionals
Opportunity to apply change skills in a data-driven, digital environment

Ad Text:
Are You Ready to Make It Happen at Mondelēz International?
Join our Mission to Lead the Future of Snacking. Make It Uniquely Yours. 

Mondelēz International empowers people to snack right in over 150 countries around the world. We're leading the future of snacking with iconic global and local brands such as Oreo, Cadbury, Philadelphia, Pascall, The Natural Confectionery Company, Belvita, Ritz and Toblerone with global revenues exceeding $36 billion USD. 


The Opportunity
You will define and evolve our climate and environment-related disclosures, leveraging cross-functional programs and roadmaps to reflect our advancements. This is an exceptional opportunity to shape the future in a dynamic environment, where your openness to learn and grow will accelerate your sustainability career.

Our Mondelēz Finance BU is a highly collaborative powerhouse, serving as custodians of an incredible portfolio of brands cherished by millions worldwide. The sheer scale of our operations in Australia & New Zealand offers unparalleled career pathways and robust learning opportunities.




About the Role:

Strategic Reporting: Develop and meticulously manage the organisation’s climate-related financial disclosure reporting processes.

Data Integrity & Transparency: Oversee the comprehensive collection, collation, verification, and transparent presentation of data pertaining to climate-related risks, opportunities, mitigation efforts, and greenhouse gas emissions.

Narrative development: Collaborate with sustainability, finance, risk, and external experts to craft compelling qualitative and quantitative disclosures on climate risks, mitigation strategies, and financial impacts across short, medium, and long-term horizons.

Cohesive Communication: Coordinate all climate and environment-related inputs for sustainability reporting and voluntary disclosures, ensuring consistency with our global 'Snacking Made Right Report'.

Policy & Procedure Enhancement: Develop and partner with process owners to enhance or establish robust policies and procedures, ensuring consistent and compliant climate and environment-related disclosures.

Timely Compliance: Prepare draft sustainability reports for thorough review, ensuring timely and compliant lodgement with all relevant regulatory bodies.




About You:

A desire to drive your future, accelerate your career, and the following experience and knowledge:

Knowledge of Australia’s climate-related financial disclosure landscape

Demonstrated experience in sustainability/climate risk reporting, financial analysis, and risk management

Advanced analytical skills

Exceptional communication skills, enabling you to convey complex climate and financial concepts with clarity to both internal and external stakeholders

Proven ability in sound, well-structured analytical problem-solving

Strong project management capabilities

A tertiary qualification in Data Analytics, Sustainability, Environmental Management, or a related field

No Relocation support available

Business Unit Summary

At Mondelez International, our mission is to provide consumers with the right snack, for the right moment, made in the right way. We are one of the largest snack companies in the world, with global net revenues exceeding $31 billion USD. 

We have operations in more than 80 countries and employ approximately 91,000 diverse and talented employees in our factories, offices, research & development facilities and distribution activities around the world.

In Australia and New Zealand, we have 6 factories, and both global and local brands, employing over 2,000 people; Cadbury Dairy Milk, Oreo, Toblerone, Philadelphia, belVita, Pascall, The Natural Confectionery Company, Sour Patch Kids and Ritz.




Mondelēz International is an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation or preference, gender identity, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.

AEMO at the Heart of Energy  

AEMO is Australia’s independent energy system and market operator and system planner. AEMO’s purpose is to ensure safe, reliable and affordable energy today, and enable the energy transition for the benefit of all Australians.  Australian governments are now committed to a net zero economy for Australia by 2050 and our vision is to enable this. We have the once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to co-design the future of our energy systems, and our core values revolve around character, commitment, and connection. Join us as we contribute to this significant transition in the energy sector.    

About the role  

AEMO’s Operations Transformation & Reform department has a pivotal role in driving forward the strategic transformation of operational capabilities to ensure readiness for evolving systems and markets. Looking ahead (up to 5 years), the department will support and enable Operations to manage energy system challenges through reform, technology, innovation and international best practice adoption. 

You will champion new ways of working, provide operations leadership on pilot projects, and foster collaboration across the business and with external partners to address real operational challenges in transformative ways. You will drive seamless coordination and alignment, and establish new ways of working. 

What you will be doing  

Manage the pipeline of potential innovation and pilot projects, working across the business to understand the requirements, the priorities, the operational impact/benefit, risks and define the approach for implementation in conjunction with operations experts and the leadership team.

Provide operations oversight and leadership on the newly established Operations Digital Incubator supporting agile delivery of small-scale technology fixes working in partnership with AEMO’s Digital division.

Collaborate with digital and with the Operations Technology and Reform program to identify suitable technology approaches for pilot projects and the wider innovation space.

Define an innovation approach and framework for Operations leading on building a culture of change and innovation.

Coach and mentor more junior team members to build a high-performing team.

What you will bring to the role  

Tertiary qualification in electrical engineering, power systems, or related discipline, with understanding of power systems and markets.

Further qualification in Project Management (e.g. CERT IV/Diploma etc), or equivalent in-house training and on the job experience.

Proven ability to deliver complex programs of engineering work.

Demonstrated experience in managing a variety of stakeholders with conflicting interests, negotiating agreed outcomes, and delivering these on time and to budget.

Ability to interpret business requirements and manage delivery.   

In return some of our benefits to you  

Flexible working: work from home, part time, job share, hybrid options, and additional leave options. 

Professional development via projects, industry networks, job rotation, study assistance and more. 

Give back with up to 4 days of volunteering leave per year. 

Reward your hard work with annual performance bonuses (subject to eligibility). 

Embrace a healthier you with our wellness program, discounted health insurance, gym perks and our comprehensive Employee Assistance Program (EAP).  

About Our Process   

At AEMO we are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workforce. We welcome people of all backgrounds, including people with disabilities and neurodivergence and those who identify as Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander. If you have any accessibility requirements to support you during the application or interview process, simply let us know by emailing us at talent@aemo.com.au

Job Title: Finance & Data Transformation Specialist | Immediate Start
Ad Text:
Job Title: Finance Transformation Lead (Multi-Entity Operations)

Are you a systems-minded Accountant who thrives on solving "broken" data flows?

We are a high-growth, multi-site operation seeking a Finance Transformation Specialist to act as the architect of our financial data. We don't just need someone to manage the books; we need someone who can build the engine that powers them.

The Challenge

Imagine a retail group with multiple storefronts where, due to system friction, a customer buys a product at "Store A," but the invoice is duplicated, and the revenue is accidentally routed to "Store B."

We are currently navigating similar complexities in our billing and payment ecosystem. We need a specialist to dive into our "data pipes," identify the leakage points, and implement a robust infrastructure to ensure every transaction is tracked, reconciled, and allocated with 100% accuracy.

Key Responsibilities

Infrastructure Development: Build and manage data infrastructure from scratch to link operational platforms with core ERP systems.
Revenue Integrity: Design and implement automated detection tools (e.g., Power BI or SQL) to flag duplicate billing and misallocated payments across various subsidiaries.
Process Re-engineering: Document and repair "broken" inter-entity reconciliation processes to ensure smooth month-end closing.
Finance-IT Liaison: Serve as the primary translator between the finance and IT teams to resolve integration issues affecting external vendor and partner invoicing.
Operational Visibility: Develop custom reports and real-time dashboards for management to provide visibility into cashflow and business performance.

About You

The Credentials: You are a Qualified Accountant (ACCA, CPA, or equivalent)
with a background in "Big 4" consulting or audit.
The Tech Stack: You are an expert in data transformation (ETL) and visualisation, proficient in tools like Power BI, SQL, or Alteryx
The Experience: You have a proven track record of handling "large volume financial data" (think billions of lines) and reducing manual turnaround times through automation.
The Mindset: You are comfortable working in an Agile environment and can coordinate stakeholders across different business units and jurisdictions.

Job description:

Your Role Please note that our office will be closed from 20 December and will reopen on 12 January 2026. • Develop and lead data migration & Analytics strategies tailored for SAP S/4HANA transformation projects.

What you'll love about working here

You will be a part of a diverse collective of free-thinkers, entrepreneurs, and industry experts. You will love the exposure to the scale of transformation, the depth of expertise, and the opportunities for career growth.
We aim to build an environment where employees can enjoy a positive work-life balance. We embed hybrid working in all that we do and make flexible working arrangements the day-to-day reality for our people.

We realise a Total Reward package should be more than just compensation. We offer a range of core and flexible benefits and have a Peer Recognition Portal called ‘Celebrate'.
We don't just believe in inclusion we actively go out to making it a working reality. Driven by our core values and ‘Inclusive future for all' campaign, we build environments where you can bring your whole self to work.

Where and how you can work

About the Team

Finance at Canva is on an exciting journey - scaling the foundations that support a rapidly growing global company, while making our processes smarter, simpler, and more empowering for our teams. The Finance Transformation team sits at the heart of this mission.

We're looking for a Finance Transformation Senior Manager who’s passionate about solving complex problems, improving processes end-to-end, and helping teams work more efficiently through technology, automation, and AI-enabled solutions. You’ll work cross-functionally across Finance, along with Finance Systems, Finance Data and the broader business, helping shape and execute Canva’s finance transformation projects — with a focus on process reengineering, driving simplification, automation and AI-driven solutions. You’ll help share the future of how Finance works at Canva.

If you love digging into business processes, running cross-functional projects, driving change, and finding opportunities to streamline and simplify — this role is made for you.

What you’ll do:

Lead Finance Process Transformation: Identify, design, and deliver scalable improvements across key global finance processes (Revenue, Billing, Payables, Reporting, etc.), balancing innovation with strong control and compliance. Help embed AI-enabled ways of working, drive adoption and education, help teams identify problems and expected outcomes - focusing on efficiency, accuracy, repeatability, and standardisation.
Project, Program and Change Management: Lead transformation programs of varying scale, ensuring cross-functional stakeholder alignment, governance, and smooth change adoption across teams. Coordinate project activities, dependencies, and timelines to ensure alignment between teams.Help unblock, remove ambiguity, and support smooth project execution.
Drive Technology Enablement: Partner with Finance Systems, Data, and Engineering teams to implement automation, system integrations, and AI-based solutions that streamline end-to-end workflows.
Help shape the Transformation Roadmap: Collaborating with finance and business leaders to define the strategic direction for the Finance Technology stack and transformation priorities.
Data, Insight & Automation: Champion data-driven decision-making - ensuring finance data is leveraged effectively for reporting, analytics, and automation.

What we're looking for

Significant experience in Finance Transformation, or Process Improvement roles (experience in fast-scaling tech, SaaS, or global environments strongly preferred).
A background in Finance with a Bachelor's degree in Finance, Accounting, Business Administration, or a related field is a big plus.
Experience with driving process redesign. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, able to break down ambiguity into actionable steps.
Familiarity with finance ERP, billing and reporting systems (e.g., Workday, Netsuite, Zuora, Salesforce, Anaplan) and an understanding of data and automation and AI platforms.
Proven ability to lead large scale transformation programs end-to-end from strategy and design to implementation and embedding.
A balance of big-picture vision and detail orientation, with a strong understanding of finance processes and data flows.
Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills; able to work cross-functionally without effort, translating between finance, technical and business teams.
Growth mindset. Passion for continuous improvement and leveraging new technologies (AI, automation, analytics) to elevate finance impact and scale finance operations.

We'd love it if you have:

Familiarity with Agile, Lean, or continuous improvement approaches.

We’re a small new team that is just getting started, so you aren’t afraid to roll up your sleeves, get into the detail. Able to determine and play whatever role is needed to make projects a success: analyst, project coordinator, facilitator, tester, or change champion.

You’ll shape the future of how finance operates at one of the world’s most loved design platforms.
You’ll work with world-class teams across Finance, IT, Data and the business in an environment that encourages experimentation and learning.
You’ll have autonomy and ownership to lead high-impact transformation initiatives that directly influence Canva’s scalability and success.
